commit.title: private poly univs in constant_body rather than constant_universes
commit.message:
private poly univs in constant_body rather than constant_universes

Mostly this avoids having to change the API for constant universes,
instead adding a field to constant_body which only the kernel really
needs to care about.

It would be even better to put them in the Opaqueproof.proofterm, but
that's beyond me. At least this commit means that we won't end up
reverting a change to constant_universes if we do that improvement later.
